<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/138.0.0.0 Safari/537.36 Edg/138.0.0.0" scale="1" border="0" version="28.0.4"> <diagram name="Page-1" id="5MhtijeboIyrWHorhBQM"> <mxGraphModel dx="1235" dy="1778" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{"data":"@startuml
title Sun, Rain & Grain: Detailed Data Processing Workflow

start

:Load Agricultural_data.csv from data/raw;
:Load climate data files for Bremen, Frankfurt, Hannover, Koeln, Leipzig, Munich, Potsdam, Stuttgart, Tegel;

partition \"Agricultural Data Cleaning\" {
 :Filter rows with null values in Agricultural_data.csv;
 :Delete rows marked as outliers (outlier = 1);
 :Aggregate sum of yearly values per district and crop category;
 :Rename columns:
 - district_no → district_id
 - var → crop_type
 - measure → measure_type;
 :Translate German attribute names to English;
 :Save cleaned agriculture dataset as agriculture_clean.csv;
}

partition \"Climate Data Cleaning (per city)\" {
 :Select columns from raw climate files:
 - STATIONS_ID
 - MESS_DATUM
 - RSK (precipitation)
 - TMK (temperature)
 - SDK (sunshine duration)
 - Delete columns: QN_3, FX, FM, QN_4, RSKF, SHK_TAG, NM, VPM, PM, UPM, TXK, TNK, TGK, eor;
 :Convert MESS_DATUM to datetime format (YYYY-MM-DD);
 :Filter data to years 1980–2020;
 :Save cleaned climate dataset per city (e.g., leipzig_clean.csv);
}

partition \"Station to District Mapping\" {
 :Load station_to_district.csv;
 :Join each climate record with district using STATIONS_ID;
 :Create climate data aggregated by district and year;
 :Save parsed climate dataset as parsed_climate.csv;
}

partition \"Data Merging\" {
 :Join agriculture_clean.csv with parsed_climate.csv on district and year;
 :Remove rows with missing data in either dataset;
 :Save merged dataset as agri_climate_merged.csv (~60,000 records);
}

partition \"Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\" {
 :Calculate correlation matrix of climate variables (RSK, TMK, SDK) vs crop yields;
 :Create lag features: TMK_lag1, RSK_lag1 (per city);
 :Calculate correlation matrices again with lagged variables;
 :Generate time series plots for crop yield and climate variables per district;
 :Create scatterplots: yield vs RSK, TMK, TMK_lag1, RSK_lag1;
 :Fit regression model: yield ~ TMK_lag1 * RSK_lag1 + year;
 :Save model summary, residuals vs fitted, and actual vs predicted plots;
 :Plot polynomial fits (degree=2): yield vs TMK, yield vs RSK;
 :Save all visualizations in outputs/eda/ and outputs/modeling/;
}

partition \"Snakemake Workflow\" {
 :Define rules for parsing, cleaning, merging, EDA, and modeling;
 :Integrate regression modeling and lag-feature analysis steps;
 :Execute pipeline with reproducibility and logging;
 :Generate outputs including plots and model summaries in outputs/;
}

stop

g.text: Sun, Rain & Grain: Detailed Data Processing Workflow
Load Agricultural_data.csv from data/raw
Load climate data files for Bremen, Frankfurt, Hannover, Koeln, Leipzig, Munich, Potsdam, Stuttgart, Tegel
Agricultural Data Cleaning
Filter rows with null values in Agricultural_data.csv
Delete rows marked as outliers (outlier = 1)
Aggregate sum of yearly values per district and crop category
Rename columns:
- district_no → district_id
- var → crop_type
- measure → measure_type
Translate German attribute names to English
Save cleaned agriculture dataset as agriculture_clean.csv
Climate Data Cleaning (per city)
Select columns from raw climate files:
- STATIONS_ID
- MESS_DATUM
- RSK (precipitation)
- TMK (temperature)
- SDK (sunshine duration)
- Delete columns: QN_3, FX, FM, QN_4, RSKF, SHK_TAG, NM, VPM, PM, UPM, TXK, TNK, TGK, eor
Convert MESS_DATUM to datetime format (YYYY-MM-DD)
Filter data to years 1980-2020
Save cleaned climate dataset per city (e.g., leipzig_clean.csv)
Station to District Mapping
Load station_to_district.csv
Join each climate record with district using STATIONS_ID
Create climate data aggregated by district and year
Save parsed climate dataset as parsed_climate.csv
Data Merging
Join agriculture_clean.csv with parsed_climate.csv on district and year
Remove rows with missing data in either dataset
Save merged dataset as agri_climate_merged.csv (~60,000 records)
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Calculate correlation matrix of climate variables (RSK, TMK, SDK) vs crop yields
Create lag features: TMK_lag1, RSK_lag1 (per city)
Calculate correlation matrices again with lagged variables
Generate time series plots for crop yield and climate variables per district
Create scatterplots: yield vs RSK, TMK, TMK_lag1, RSK_lag1
Fit regression model: yield ~ TMK_lag1 * RSK_lag1 + year
Save model summary, residuals vs fitted, and actual vs predicted plots
Plot polynomial fits (degree=2): yield vs TMK, yield vs RSK
Save all visualizations in outputs/eda/ and outputs/modeling/
Snakemake Workflow
Define rules for parsing, cleaning, merging, EDA, and modeling
Integrate regression modeling and lag-feature analysis steps
Execute pipeline with reproducibility and logging
Generate outputs including plots and model summaries in outputs/
